WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:15.135
Can I help you?

3
00:04:24.847 --> 00:04:27.517
This guy goes to the doctor for a checkup.

4
00:04:28.476 --> 00:04:31.271
After a while. the doc says.

5
00:04:32.230 --> 00:04:35.108
"Sir. you'll have to stop masturbating."

6
00:04:35.191 --> 00:04:36.985
"Why? What for?"

7
00:04:37.485 --> 00:04:39.153
"I'm examining you."

8
00:04:47.912 --> 00:04:49.789
Another guy goes to his doc.

9
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:52.542
"You said it was urgent. Doc."

10
00:04:52.625 --> 00:04:55.962
"Yes. I have good news and bad news."

11
00:04:56.045 --> 00:04:57.755
"Start with the bad."

12
00:04:57.839 --> 00:05:00.049
"You only have a week to live."

13
00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:01.968
"Shit! And the good news?"

14
00:05:02.677 --> 00:05:07.098
"My secretary agreed to go out
with me this weekend."

15
00:08:24.629 --> 00:08:26.088
Stop! Stop!

16
00:08:29.634 --> 00:08:30.635
Back up. Keep going.

17
00:09:10.758 --> 00:09:12.593
It's Janie and her daughter.

18
00:09:14.053 --> 00:09:16.264
The girl went to school with mine.

19
00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:45.793
Come on. we'll do it next time.

20
00:10:14.155 --> 00:10:15.448
Come on!

21
00:10:30.004 --> 00:10:31.130
What are you doing?

22
00:11:47.706 --> 00:11:49.166
Vézina!

23
00:12:47.683 --> 00:12:48.642
Jesus fucking...

24
00:13:43.197 --> 00:13:44.990
I shouldn't have hesitated.

25
00:13:47.743 --> 00:13:50.329
But when it's your wife. you think twice.

26
00:14:04.927 --> 00:14:07.555
One just got his surveyor's diploma.

27
00:14:08.764 --> 00:14:10.891
The other loved to monkey around.

28
00:14:12.142 --> 00:14:13.519
Two nice boys.

29
00:14:27.324 --> 00:14:28.909
If I'd known...

30
00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:31.203
I told you not to.

31
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:34.039
No. if I'd known...

32
00:14:34.582 --> 00:14:35.666
Known what?

33
00:14:36.458 --> 00:14:39.169
I'd have emptied my bank account

34
00:14:39.253 --> 00:14:42.464
and taken my kid to see Mickey Mouse
like I promised.

35
00:14:43.257 --> 00:14:44.258
You?

36
00:14:48.762 --> 00:14:51.056
-You know Turgeon's girl?
-Katy?

37
00:14:51.140 --> 00:14:52.057
Yeah.

38
00:14:54.101 --> 00:14:55.728
I'd have gone to her door

39
00:14:56.645 --> 00:14:58.230
with a big bouquet.

40
00:14:58.314 --> 00:14:59.732
I'd have said to her.

41
00:15:01.317 --> 00:15:02.526
"Hey. Katy. you know what?

42
00:15:06.572 --> 00:15:08.532
I always liked you.

43
00:15:09.700 --> 00:15:12.578
What are you doing
with that loser Turgeon?"

44
00:15:14.580 --> 00:15:17.833
She'd have slugged me. She hated my guts.

45
00:15:17.917 --> 00:15:20.419
At school. you made fun of her braces.

46
00:15:22.129 --> 00:15:24.715
It was my way of showing I liked her.

47
00:15:24.798 --> 00:15:26.050
Dumb.

48
00:15:26.133 --> 00:15:28.802
-I know.
-No.

49
00:15:28.886 --> 00:15:30.888
The idea of going to her place.

50
00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:34.308
Of all the possibilities.
you'd choose that?

51
00:15:37.519 --> 00:15:40.981
No wonder you prefer Roger Moore
to Sean Connery.

52
00:15:41.565 --> 00:15:44.026
Not like Walt Disney isn't predictable.

53
00:15:44.109 --> 00:15:45.861
The sky's the limit.

54
00:15:45.945 --> 00:15:49.782
and you choose to go see a giant mouse
with a stupid smile.

55
00:15:50.449 --> 00:15:53.327
And I'd get slapped by Katy Valère...

56
00:15:56.288 --> 00:15:58.749
Yup. our lives don't amount to much.

57
00:17:08.277 --> 00:17:09.695
Need something?

58
00:17:12.614 --> 00:17:14.408
You're going to have to strip.

59
00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:16.201
Pardon?

60
00:17:16.994 --> 00:17:19.455
To see if you've been bitten. hon.

61
00:17:41.727 --> 00:17:43.270
Can I get you a beer?

62
00:17:49.610 --> 00:17:51.403
What's left out there?

63
00:17:54.907 --> 00:17:57.659
You're the first survivors
I've met in days.

64
00:18:10.172 --> 00:18:11.840
Take as long as you need.

65
00:18:45.332 --> 00:18:46.667
What do you want?

66
00:18:47.918 --> 00:18:49.711
It's my hunting camp. too.

67
00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:54.174
Vézina's not with you?

68
00:19:37.050 --> 00:19:38.302
Fucking Vézina.

69
00:19:39.094 --> 00:19:42.890
He puts down his entire family
and still managed to laugh.

70
00:19:45.267 --> 00:19:46.351
That's Vézina.

71
00:19:48.103 --> 00:19:49.271
And Steevy?

72
00:19:50.397 --> 00:19:54.109
Two days ago. we saw smoke at Darveau's.
and he went to look.

73
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:56.153
He hasn't come back?

74
00:19:58.780 --> 00:20:00.240
Maybe he got bitten.

75
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:01.658
I'd be surprised.

76
00:20:05.078 --> 00:20:06.205
Where you going?

77
00:20:19.218 --> 00:20:21.053
Does Thérèse know about her boy?

78
00:20:22.262 --> 00:20:23.931
You better tell her.

79
00:20:25.265 --> 00:20:27.267
She sure made great muffins.

80
00:20:28.727 --> 00:20:30.812
There's a girl tied to my bunk.

81
00:20:32.481 --> 00:20:33.607
Why's she there?

82
00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:36.109
She claims a dog bit her.

83
00:20:43.659 --> 00:20:46.203
Try not to make too much noise
with your pickup.

84
00:20:53.335 --> 00:20:55.254
Want to know what'll happen?

85
00:20:59.341 --> 00:21:01.218
At first. you'll feel weird.

86
00:21:03.720 --> 00:21:07.140
Does it come from the water.
the air. our genes?

87
00:21:07.224 --> 00:21:08.225
Who knows?

88
00:21:11.061 --> 00:21:12.813
You'll think it's a headache.

89
00:21:14.564 --> 00:21:16.108
You'll feel nauseous.

90
00:21:18.694 --> 00:21:19.945
The next day.

91
00:21:20.779 --> 00:21:23.115
you'll get blotches on your skin.

92
00:21:24.658 --> 00:21:26.451
You'll want to see the doctor.

93
00:21:28.912 --> 00:21:31.915
Like everyone else.
he's vanished into thin air.

94
00:21:35.502 --> 00:21:37.129
Another day goes by.

95
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.633
You start to feel stronger.

96
00:21:43.051 --> 00:21:46.346
Even if your fingers turn black
and you spit up molasses.

97
00:21:48.765 --> 00:21:51.268
The next thing you realize...

98
00:21:52.769 --> 00:21:55.105
you're kneeling on the kitchen floor.

99
00:21:56.315 --> 00:21:58.984
gnawing on your kid's guts.

100
00:22:07.034 --> 00:22:09.369
I can't hear. He plugged my ears.

101
00:22:13.832 --> 00:22:15.375
Wait. Wait!

102
00:22:15.917 --> 00:22:17.961
Don't go!

103
00:22:18.045 --> 00:22:19.379
Please! Please!

104
00:22:19.463 --> 00:22:20.630
Come here!

105
00:22:27.054 --> 00:22:29.264
-A dog really bit you?
-Yes.

106
00:22:29.347 --> 00:22:31.266
-Tell me the truth.
-I swear.

107
00:22:31.349 --> 00:22:33.310
If it was them. would you say?

108
00:22:33.393 --> 00:22:35.812
No. I mean. yes! Yes!

109
00:22:36.396 --> 00:22:37.397
Wait!

110
00:22:40.067 --> 00:22:45.072
Jesus fucking Christ!

111
00:25:33.698 --> 00:25:34.574
The gun!

112
00:25:36.409 --> 00:25:37.494
Shoot!

113
00:25:38.245 --> 00:25:39.204
Shoot! Fuck!

114
00:26:31.256 --> 00:26:33.008
You didn't want a gun?

115
00:26:40.890 --> 00:26:42.142
That's my map.

116
00:27:12.922 --> 00:27:14.299
I've never seen you before.

117
00:27:15.800 --> 00:27:17.427
My dad has a cabin on Trout Lake.

118
00:28:09.396 --> 00:28:10.397
Gotcha!

119
00:28:10.480 --> 00:28:12.607
Fucking Bonin. works every time.

120
00:28:14.317 --> 00:28:17.570
Bonin. Bonin. Bonin... You never change.

121
00:28:17.654 --> 00:28:18.696
Sure don't.

122
00:28:20.907 --> 00:28:21.908
So. Bonin...

123
00:28:23.576 --> 00:28:25.578
you've been busy while I was away.

124
00:28:26.329 --> 00:28:29.707
So the nerd does more
than just read science.

125
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:32.210
It's science fiction. Demers.

126
00:28:32.961 --> 00:28:35.004
-What's up?
-Not much.

127
00:28:36.256 --> 00:28:38.174
By the way.

128
00:28:38.258 --> 00:28:40.135
I ran into Gingras' mom.

129
00:28:41.970 --> 00:28:43.722
-What's with her?
-What do you mean?

130
00:28:43.805 --> 00:28:45.014
She tried to bite me.

131
00:28:47.934 --> 00:28:49.227
Did she get you?

132
00:28:49.310 --> 00:28:50.562
No.

133
00:28:52.230 --> 00:28:57.068
Well. I'll be going. Surprise the family.
The prodigy son's returned!

134
00:28:57.152 --> 00:28:58.486
Prodigal son.

135
00:28:58.570 --> 00:28:59.529
Prodigy.

136
00:28:59.612 --> 00:29:01.322
-No. prodigal.
-Prodigy.

137
00:29:02.824 --> 00:29:03.867
Well. then.

138
00:29:05.952 --> 00:29:06.953
Bye for now!

139
00:29:08.455 --> 00:29:10.290
Bye. Demers.

140
00:29:10.999 --> 00:29:12.709
The guy's clueless.

141
00:29:13.501 --> 00:29:16.504
Thinks he's back from a mission
he never went on.

142
00:29:31.019 --> 00:29:34.397
The radio said to wait for help.
but it never came.

143
00:29:38.234 --> 00:29:40.320
My emotions got the best of me.

144
00:29:42.030 --> 00:29:43.323
Big mistake.

145
00:29:48.369 --> 00:29:51.039
When I tried to flee my wife and sons.

146
00:29:51.998 --> 00:29:54.834
all I wanted was to turn
and yell. "I love you."

147
00:29:58.755 --> 00:29:59.923
Stupid. huh?

148
00:30:07.555 --> 00:30:08.681
Not really.

149
00:31:17.667 --> 00:31:20.211
GINGRAS FARM

150
00:36:50.291 --> 00:36:52.376
So a guy comes to work looking sad.

151
00:36:53.586 --> 00:36:55.129
"Why so glum?"

152
00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:57.673
"My wife left me this morning."

153
00:36:58.549 --> 00:37:01.302
"You two seemed so happy. What happened?"

154
00:37:02.762 --> 00:37:05.806
"I had a slip of the tongue.
and she left."

155
00:37:06.432 --> 00:37:07.558
"What did you say?"

156
00:37:08.517 --> 00:37:11.687
"Instead of saying.
'Pass the salt. my love.'

157
00:37:11.771 --> 00:37:14.315
I went. 'You ruined my life. you cow.'"

158
00:37:23.950 --> 00:37:25.576
I wanted to make her laugh.

159
00:37:35.127 --> 00:37:36.379
<i>You there. my pup?</i>

160
00:37:38.297 --> 00:37:39.298
Who's that?

161
00:37:39.382 --> 00:37:41.092
<i>My little pup. you there?</i>

162
00:37:44.470 --> 00:37:45.471
<i>Little pup?</i> Over.

163
00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:08.369
She doesn't look like
she's ever cooked with Crisco.

164
00:38:10.955 --> 00:38:14.125
She can bathe in orange water
if she wants.

165
00:38:14.208 --> 00:38:17.420
Seeing how she holds that rifle.
I feel pretty safe.

166
00:41:30.863 --> 00:41:34.450
I want to go to work!
Why am I saying this?

167
00:41:34.533 --> 00:41:36.827
I have a friend named Katy.
She owns a sex shop.

168
00:41:36.911 --> 00:41:40.998
On hot days like today.
we stand outside in bikinis.

169
00:41:41.081 --> 00:41:43.042
Truckers stop to buy
something for the wife.

170
00:41:43.125 --> 00:41:46.837
Of course they ogle us.
Katy has business smarts.

171
00:41:46.921 --> 00:41:48.297
And I'll never see her again.

172
00:41:48.380 --> 00:41:52.259
I'm stuck in the jungle
with a cornball comic.

173
00:41:52.343 --> 00:41:55.387
And little Zoé. At least you're here...

174
00:41:55.471 --> 00:41:57.306
Pretty Zoé. so mysterious.

175
00:42:04.104 --> 00:42:06.649
Lucky you. you're mysterious.

176
00:42:06.732 --> 00:42:08.901
Me. I'm the cornball comic.

177
00:42:15.366 --> 00:42:17.868
Me. it's my friend Ti-Guy who I miss.

178
00:42:18.869 --> 00:42:20.746
He's my favorite cousin.

179
00:42:21.580 --> 00:42:23.249
We go on bicycle rides

180
00:42:23.332 --> 00:42:24.333
and play hockey.

181
00:42:24.917 --> 00:42:27.086
He passes to me so I can score.

182
00:42:27.670 --> 00:42:28.879
I'm pretty good.

183
00:42:32.550 --> 00:42:34.093
You'll see Ti-Guy again.

184
00:42:35.427 --> 00:42:36.845
Yeah. when I'm dead.

185
00:42:44.103 --> 00:42:45.187
That's a good one!

186
00:42:45.271 --> 00:42:46.647
I got you again.

187
00:42:46.730 --> 00:42:49.525
The look on your faces!
Wish I had a photo.

188
00:42:51.777 --> 00:42:54.238
Demers. have you finished. damn it?

189
00:42:57.241 --> 00:42:59.285
Hey. Bonin. you...

190
00:42:59.868 --> 00:43:03.205
Looks like your family's growing.

191
00:43:06.292 --> 00:43:09.086
I don't wanna scare you.
but if you ask me.

192
00:43:10.212 --> 00:43:12.298
something's up on Route 8.

193
00:44:48.394 --> 00:44:49.520
Don't go.

194
00:44:50.312 --> 00:44:51.480
I'll be back. okay?

195
00:47:41.984 --> 00:47:42.985
Can we get out?

196
00:47:44.695 --> 00:47:46.196
We'll wait a bit. okay?

197
00:47:58.375 --> 00:48:01.169
You're still grieving
and you lose someone else.

198
00:48:09.386 --> 00:48:10.637
My little pup.

199
00:48:14.641 --> 00:48:15.559
Thérèse...

200
00:48:22.608 --> 00:48:23.984
What I saw out there...

201
00:48:26.903 --> 00:48:28.322
I've never seen that.

202
00:48:39.708 --> 00:48:42.169
For weeks we've survived.

203
00:48:42.252 --> 00:48:43.545
We almost felt comfortable.

204
00:48:43.629 --> 00:48:45.714
We saw fewer and fewer of them.

205
00:48:49.134 --> 00:48:51.053
Why'd they come back? What happened?

206
00:48:51.136 --> 00:48:52.721
They had no choice.

207
00:48:52.804 --> 00:48:53.847
What do you mean?

208
00:48:54.931 --> 00:48:56.475
They had nothing to eat.

209
00:48:57.225 --> 00:48:58.977
So they came back home.

210
00:48:59.061 --> 00:49:01.855
Someone must be blocking their way.

211
00:49:01.938 --> 00:49:03.315
What about the city?

212
00:49:03.398 --> 00:49:05.859
We have more chance of survival there.

213
00:49:08.779 --> 00:49:10.197
You did good here.

214
00:49:10.280 --> 00:49:13.909
But the government will
protect cities before villages.

215
00:49:13.992 --> 00:49:16.119
You saying we ain't worth shit?

216
00:49:16.787 --> 00:49:18.747
As PM. I'd do the same.

217
00:49:18.830 --> 00:49:20.332
Good to know.

218
00:49:20.415 --> 00:49:23.418
Remind me not to vote for you
if you ever run.

219
00:49:26.088 --> 00:49:28.465
We'll barricade the windows better.

220
00:49:29.925 --> 00:49:32.219
Save our ammo. Not make noise.

221
00:49:33.178 --> 00:49:35.222
We're low on food.

222
00:49:35.806 --> 00:49:38.350
If we tighten our belt. we'll make it.

223
00:49:40.352 --> 00:49:41.895
Not you. kitten.

224
00:49:43.522 --> 00:49:47.901
You can eat your fill.
You're still growing.

225
00:49:47.984 --> 00:49:49.569
You can't stay here.

226
00:49:53.907 --> 00:49:56.660
Or use the road the army didn't block.

227
00:49:59.287 --> 00:50:02.624
Those creatures are gathering.
There's no other way.

228
00:50:04.418 --> 00:50:06.920
The house is right on their path.

229
00:50:08.672 --> 00:50:10.257
They know we're here. <i>I know a bunker.</i>

230
00:50:25.188 --> 00:50:28.734
We have to skirt the farms on Route 8.

231
00:50:29.317 --> 00:50:30.986
reach the Demers River.

232
00:50:31.069 --> 00:50:33.238
follow Muddy Creek.

233
00:50:33.864 --> 00:50:36.116
take the fork to the dam.

234
00:50:36.199 --> 00:50:38.827
then cross the forest on foot.

235
00:50:38.910 --> 00:50:40.162
What if there's nothing there?

236
00:50:40.245 --> 00:50:42.748
What if it's too late?
And someone's already using it?

237
00:50:55.635 --> 00:50:56.887
It's a dog bite.

238
00:51:14.529 --> 00:51:16.156
A jar of pickles. at least.

239
00:51:17.282 --> 00:51:18.283
Dill pickles?

240
00:51:18.366 --> 00:51:20.327
Yeah. they're so good.

241
00:51:22.537 --> 00:51:24.289
There's not enough to go around.

242
00:51:24.915 --> 00:51:26.708
Those jars hold a lot.

243
00:51:26.792 --> 00:51:27.918
Take two.

244
00:51:28.001 --> 00:51:29.669
We don't have room.

245
00:51:30.337 --> 00:51:32.380
I'd take some of this.

246
00:51:33.507 --> 00:51:34.716
Yeah. your jelly...

247
00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:36.301
Crab apple.

248
00:51:36.384 --> 00:51:38.345
-They're almost sweet.
-It's good.

249
00:51:38.428 --> 00:51:40.680
Nothing better. Here. hide it.

250
00:52:28.395 --> 00:52:29.813
I wonder where they are.

251
00:52:32.065 --> 00:52:33.066
Who? My family.

252
00:52:37.487 --> 00:52:39.281
Where do you think they are?

253
00:52:42.200 --> 00:52:44.828
Not partying on a beach in Cuba. I hope.

254
00:52:44.911 --> 00:52:46.037
That would suck.

255
00:52:48.957 --> 00:52:53.253
As soon as we touch on something serious.
you change the subject.

256
00:52:56.923 --> 00:52:59.134
I'll only stop when I stop believing.

257
00:53:00.051 --> 00:53:03.054
There's nothing left
to believe in. anyway.

258
00:53:04.306 --> 00:53:05.724
Why do you play dumb?

259
00:53:05.807 --> 00:53:08.184
When I start to think. I see them.

260
00:53:08.810 --> 00:53:10.312
I don't want to see them.

261
00:53:13.565 --> 00:53:14.566
Who?

262
00:53:15.483 --> 00:53:17.402
It reminds me how they saw me.

263
00:53:19.362 --> 00:53:21.197
The black sheep of the family.

264
00:53:24.784 --> 00:53:27.662
And I'm the last one alive.
What's the message?

265
00:53:35.921 --> 00:53:38.757
I'm just saying
you can be loved for who you are.

266
00:53:42.385 --> 00:53:43.470
Well. well. well.

267
00:54:00.987 --> 00:54:02.364
Why are you whispering?

268
00:54:05.492 --> 00:54:07.619
We're talking about your hand. hon.

269
00:54:08.495 --> 00:54:10.121
What about my hand?

270
00:54:10.705 --> 00:54:11.998
It's worrisome.

271
00:54:13.708 --> 00:54:15.418
Did you tell 'em it was a dog? I was trying to explain that.

272
00:54:19.547 --> 00:54:20.882
But you weren't there.

273
00:54:22.926 --> 00:54:24.094
No. I wasn't there.

274
00:54:27.514 --> 00:54:29.557
Next time you're deciding my fate.

275
00:54:29.641 --> 00:54:32.811
I'd like to be involved. if that's okay.

276
00:54:32.894 --> 00:54:34.104
Look. hon...

277
00:54:34.187 --> 00:54:36.773
We're concerned. That's all.

278
00:54:36.856 --> 00:54:39.567
I'm not your hon. Pauline. Or anybody's.

279
00:54:55.083 --> 00:54:56.292
I heard something.

280
00:55:07.971 --> 00:55:08.972
Where was it?

281
00:55:16.104 --> 00:55:17.230
What are you doing?

282
00:56:27.133 --> 00:56:28.134
Let's go! Hurry!

283
00:57:29.737 --> 00:57:30.780
Zoé. let's go!

284
01:03:37.522 --> 01:03:41.901
If you hear a growl.
you turn towards it. pump and fire.

285
01:03:42.443 --> 01:03:45.571
-Don't think twice. Got it?
-I turn and fire.

286
01:03:46.405 --> 01:03:47.490
First you pump.

287
01:03:48.032 --> 01:03:49.242
Right. first I pump.

288
01:03:52.411 --> 01:03:54.372
Don't forget the safety.

289
01:03:55.373 --> 01:03:58.251
-or it won't fire.
-Okay. the safety.

290
01:03:58.334 --> 01:04:01.963
It's right here.
It's red. meaning you can shoot.

291
01:04:02.672 --> 01:04:05.591
So. it's the opposite of traffic lights.

292
01:04:06.634 --> 01:04:07.635
I guess.

293
01:04:08.553 --> 01:04:09.971
So now I can fire?

294
01:04:10.721 --> 01:04:12.515
It'd be better with ammo.

295
01:04:14.058 --> 01:04:15.142
I think it's safe.

296
01:04:17.562 --> 01:04:19.146
There's no other route?

297
01:04:20.064 --> 01:04:23.067
The river. but that would add another day.

298
01:04:25.111 --> 01:04:28.030
What if they surprise us in the field?

299
01:04:28.698 --> 01:04:31.117
We run into the forest past the road.

300
01:04:33.536 --> 01:04:37.290
I'll never make it.
I'll be wheezing like the devil.

301
01:04:37.373 --> 01:04:39.625
I can carry you. if need be.

302
01:04:40.960 --> 01:04:44.630
Kid. it's been 45 years
since anybody carried me.

303
01:04:44.714 --> 01:04:47.300
I think I can survive one more day.

304
01:05:44.523 --> 01:05:46.817
I was just trying to...

305
01:06:03.167 --> 01:06:04.460
I thought it was...

306
01:06:04.543 --> 01:06:05.920
You did good.

307
01:06:07.004 --> 01:06:08.089
He'd been bitten.

308
01:06:10.549 --> 01:06:12.635
Yeah. he'd been bitten. Anyway. he was infected.

309
01:06:21.310 --> 01:06:22.436
Come on. kitten.

310
01:08:24.391 --> 01:08:25.768
My name's Réal.

311
01:08:26.519 --> 01:08:28.437
You may've seen me in the paper.

312
01:08:29.897 --> 01:08:31.398
I sell insurance.

313
01:08:33.400 --> 01:08:35.069
Last time I heard. he was...

314
01:08:35.611 --> 01:08:36.654
Ti-Cul.

315
01:09:51.896 --> 01:09:53.439
Have you ever killed someone?

316
01:09:54.356 --> 01:09:55.357
Yeah.

317
01:09:56.442 --> 01:09:57.651
Bet it's not easy.

318
01:09:57.735 --> 01:09:58.736
No.

319
01:10:00.362 --> 01:10:01.864
But it's better than nothing.

320
01:10:02.448 --> 01:10:03.449
Maybe.

321
01:10:04.033 --> 01:10:05.242
I say it is.

322
01:13:33.784 --> 01:13:37.079
"To all visitors
who happen to pass by here:

323
01:13:38.330 --> 01:13:42.376
If. for any reason.
you're planning to go into town.

324
01:13:43.001 --> 01:13:44.086
don't go there.

325
01:13:45.671 --> 01:13:48.674
It's crawling with those evil things.

326
01:13:49.508 --> 01:13:52.678
Everyone I managed to escape with
has been taken.

327
01:13:54.012 --> 01:13:55.347
I'm the last one left.

328
01:13:57.599 --> 01:13:59.518
I haven't seen anyone in weeks.

329
01:14:00.227 --> 01:14:04.148
Every day. I go out on Route 113
looking for survivors.

330
01:14:04.773 --> 01:14:06.108
I haven't lost hope."

331
01:14:08.527 --> 01:14:10.320
Signed. Number 79.

332
01:16:44.099 --> 01:16:47.185
I had to leave them at home
with their dad that day.

333
01:16:48.854 --> 01:16:49.938
Why?

334
01:16:52.524 --> 01:16:54.985
To go for a manicure.

335
01:17:07.873 --> 01:17:11.460
When I made love.
it was all about playing the good wife.

336
01:17:13.712 --> 01:17:15.881
I was the woman I'd been trained to be.

337
01:17:17.132 --> 01:17:18.508
The perfect woman.

338
01:17:20.677 --> 01:17:22.012
The strong woman.

339
01:17:34.399 --> 01:17:35.776
But these days.

340
01:17:37.569 --> 01:17:39.196
not much bothers me.

341
01:17:49.831 --> 01:17:50.832
Rémi.

342
01:17:52.668 --> 01:17:54.544
My name's Rémi Latraverse.

343
01:18:48.181 --> 01:18:49.516
My pickles...

344
01:18:52.185 --> 01:18:54.229
Did I put in too much dill?

345
01:18:59.860 --> 01:19:01.236
Don't think so.

346
01:21:14.202 --> 01:21:15.287
When you wake up

347
01:21:15.370 --> 01:21:17.747
and the first thing you do
is kill someone...

348
01:21:21.668 --> 01:21:23.211
you know it's a whole new world.

349
01:27:25.573 --> 01:27:28.451
Don't tell the others.
but you're the strongest.

350
01:30:45.064 --> 01:30:46.232
Where's Tania?

351
01:30:54.365 --> 01:30:56.033
Go find Tania. okay?

352
01:30:57.160 --> 01:30:58.161
Okay.

353
01:30:59.912 --> 01:31:01.414
So you won't be alone.

354
01:31:01.497 --> 01:31:02.540
No.

355
01:31:06.586 --> 01:31:08.296
You know that you have to go.

356
01:31:16.387 --> 01:31:18.347
This guy goes to the doctor's.

357
01:31:20.600 --> 01:31:22.643
He says. "Doc. something's wrong.

358
01:31:26.439 --> 01:31:28.733
If I press against my heart. it hurts.

359
01:31:31.861 --> 01:31:33.654
When I rub my stomach.

360
01:31:34.238 --> 01:31:35.907
the pain is intense.

361
01:31:38.451 --> 01:31:40.453
If I touch my throat. it's worse.

362
01:31:44.290 --> 01:31:46.167
Doc. do you know what I have?"

363
01:31:50.379 --> 01:31:51.672
"Yes. sir.

364
01:31:53.299 --> 01:31:54.967
Your finger's broken."

365
01:36:18.647 --> 01:36:19.815
Don't go that way.

366
01:36:27.990 --> 01:36:28.991
Thanks.

367
01:36:31.243 --> 01:36:32.578
Are you an astronaut?

368
01:36:34.997 --> 01:36:36.040
A gun...

368
01:36:37.305 --> 01:37:37.264
Tired of searching for subtitles?
Ray generates them instantly: getray.app
